### Part 2: Data Usage Guidelines - Securing What You Share

Even the strongest prompts won’t matter if unsafe data is sent to the model.  
Equally important is knowing **what data can and cannot be shared** during experimentation, prototyping, and production.  

Here are the SAP data usage guidelines:  

#### 1. Experimentation
- Use the [Generative AI Experience Lab](https://sapit-home-prod-004.launchpad.cfapps.eu10.hana.ondemand.com/site#GenAIXL-Display?mobilestart.tile.hidden=true&sap-ui-app-id-hint=d77a57f8-167d-4050-b0ab-3ed131ec48fb) for experimentation.
  - **Public data:** Can be sent to all models.  
  - **Internal data:** Can be sent to all models, except those in *preview*.  
  - **Confidential data:** Can be sent to all models, except those in *preview*.  
  - **Personal data:** Cannot be sent (includes SAP customer data, SAP employee data, or customer personal data).  

#### 2. Prototyping and Productization for Product Development
- For building POCs, API-based experiments and testing, and productizing use cases, use the [Generative AI Hub in SAP AI Core](https://help.sap.com/docs/sap-ai-core/sap-ai-core-service-guide/generative-ai-hub-in-sap-ai-core-7db524ee75e74bf8b50c167951fe34a5).
  - **Public data:** Can be sent to all models.  
  - **Internal data:** Can be sent to all models.  
  - **Confidential data:** Can be sent to all models.  
  - **Personal data:** Allowed only during productization (if respective product standards like DPP-362, SEC-380, etc. are followed), but **never during experimentation**.   


> **Key takeaway:** Prompt Hardening protects the *how*, while Data Usage Guidelines protect the *what*. Both are essential for securing LLM applications.
